Aux:TextAnnotations.Aux:document_text: PtS Plc has announced VTune 4.0 Performance Enhancement Environment, a development tool for processor optimization for Pentium III. The new version of VTune Performance Analyser included in v4.0 provides software analysis and tuning for the Pentium III and earlier generations; an upgrade to the Intel C/C++ compiler; new versions of the Intel Performance libraries; and online training and documentation on the Pentium III, streaming SIMD extensions, MMX technology, and other Intel processors for quick reference. VTune 4.0 also provides a native Java compiler called the Bytecode Analyser, which allows programmers to identify and optimize Java programs. VTune 4.0 costs 299 pounds sterling. For more information, contact PtS Plc, +44.0.1928.579900; fax +44.0.1928.579901; info@pts.com; www.pts.com. M Squared Technologies Releases Resource Standard Metrics v4 M Squared Technologies has announced Resource Standard Metrics (RSM) v4, a source-code metrics and quality analysis tool for C, ANSI C, and Java for use on Windows 95/98/NT and Unix operating systems. RSM performs source-code metrics for lines of code, comment percentage, keywords and constructs, logical and interface functional complexity, and class metrics. Additionally, RSM performs metrics on the function, class, file, project, and code tree. RSM can also run lines of code metrics between two date-dependent code baselines yielding lines of code and file differentials.
